title: Fed Chair Powell's job is safe 'at the present time,' Larry Kudlow says
text: The Trump administration is making "no effort" to remove the Fed's Jerome Powell, top White House economic advisor Larry Kudlow said on Tuesday.

title: Fed Chairman Powell's job is 'safe,' White House's Kudlow says
text: Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell's job is "safe" and "there is no effort to remove him," said White House National Economic Council Director Larry Kudlow on Tuesday. Kudlow was speaking at a CNBC event.

title: Get a Bigger Picture of US Housing Market With This New ETF
text: The housing fund HOMZ hit the market in March. Let's take a look how this new ETF is different from the two longstanding products in the space.

title: Renewi: High-Risk High-Reward?
text: Renewi is a UK-listed garbage processor generating the majority of its revenue in Belgium and the Netherlands.

title: Virgin Galactic: Space tourism flights to begin in a year, company will be profitable in 2021
text: Virgin Group founder Richard Branson and venture capitalist Chamath Palihapitiya spoke to CNBC's "Squawk Box" on Tuesday.

title: Wisconsin governor says Foxconn is again likely to miss job targets
text: Gov. Tony Evers reveals that the Foxconn manufacturing complex planned in Wisconsin is likely to continue falling short of the threshold required to begin receiving billions of dollars in state incentives, even after production begins next year.

title: Richard Branson's Virgin Galactic plans to go public by end of 2019
text: Billionaire Richard Branson's space-tourism venture, Virgin Galactic, plans to public by the end of this year as part of a deal with a special purpose acquisition company (SPAC) created by venture-capital firms Social Capital and Hedosophia, the companies said on Tuesday.

title: Grocery chain Lidl to install over 4,000 solar panels at distribution facility in Ireland
text: The major retailer is aiming to green its operations through the use of solar power.

title: Virgin Galactic reportedly prepares for public trading launch     - CNET
text: It'll make Richard Branson's venture the first publicly listed space-tourism company, according to the Wall Street Journal.

title: Stocks Slip With U.S. Futures As Treasuries Drift: Markets Wrap
text: European shares and U.S. stock futures retreated alongside Asian equities as markets extended a downbeat start to the week.

title: Wall Street Strategists See Stocks Falling in Major Reversal
text: These habitually bullish market watchers have turned bearish, clouding the outlook for stocks.

title: Bitcoin near two-week highs, fueled by hopes for Facebook's Libra
text: Bitcoin held on Tuesday near its highest for two weeks after surging as much as 9% overnight, a move analysts said was probably driven by hopes that cryptocurrencies are gaining wider acceptance after Facebook disclosed plans for a digital coin.

title: Multibillion-dollar Singaporean investing giant says its returns have taken a major hit
text: Singaporean state investment firm Temasek Holdings on Tuesday reported a plunge in its returns over a one-year period amid a challenging economic environment compounded by trade tensions between the U.S. and China.

title: Nexon founder scraps what could have been $16 billion gaming deal: sources
text: Nexon Co  founder Jungju Kim has abandoned plans to sell a controlling stake in its parent NXC, two sources with direct knowledge of the matter said, scuppering a potentially $16 billion deal that would have been the gaming sector's biggest.

title: Richard Branson's Virgin Galactic plans to go public: source
text: Richard Branson's space-tourism venture, Virgin Galactic, is planning to go public as part of a deal with a special-purpose acquisition company (SPAC) created by Social Capital LP Chief Executive Officer Chamath Palihapitiya, a person familiar with the matter said.
